race.comment: CAMBO'S ETHICS (3) has a strong record this trip with six wins and two placings from nine starts. Recorded a 3 length win (17.61) in a NG last time at this track. Looks suited here and rates on top. RUINATION (2) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (17.85) at this track behind CAMBO'S ETHICS in a NG. Settled off speed and worked to the line nicely. Hard to beat again. RED OPAL (1) turned in a fair 5th placed finish last time at Maitland over 450m (25.31). Should be about the money. VILIAME (6) has ability and finds the right scenario to bounce back.
